Det Con Neil Cunnington said: "We would like to hear from anyone who was in the area of Co-op this morning and saw a man dressed in dark clothing, carrying a holdall.
"He appears to have been struggling to carry the bag as he took a large quantity of coins and we have reports of him staggering due to the weight.
"No-one was hurt during the robbery and the shop has been examined for forensic evidence."
